<body>
    <h1>Query Explorer API Contract</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"5b0b0760103f" id=3D"QueryExplorerAPIContract-TL;DR"=
>TL;DR</h2>
<p local-id=3D"360b28548eaa">This page describes how the <strong>Query Expl=
orer </strong>frontend communicates with the backend Query API using a <str=
ong>GraphQL-style request/response format</strong>. Queries are sent to the=
 <code>POST /query</code> endpoint as a GraphQL-like query string with opti=
onal variables, and the API returns results in a standard GraphQL-style env=
elope containing <code>data</code> and <code>errors</code>. The page also d=
escribes the <strong>Autocomplete Metadata API (</strong><code>GET /query/s=
chema</code><strong>)</strong>, which provides a schema describing availabl=
e query types, fields, and arguments so the editor can generate context-awa=
re autocomplete suggestions.</p>
<p local-id=3D"61da118ff53e"><strong>Limitations:</strong> The query API fo=
llows a GraphQL-style structure but is not a full GraphQL server, so some b=
ehaviors may differ from standard GraphQL implementations. Autocomplete rel=
ies on a <strong>schema snapshot loaded at editor initialization</strong>, =
meaning schema changes require a page reload to appear, and suggestions are=
 schema-based only, so they cannot validate runtime conditions (e.g., wheth=
er a repository, ref, or file actually exists).</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"f6e3e7d6e363" id=3D"QueryExplorerAPIContract-QueryAPI">Quer=
y API</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"b863c6ece809" id=3D"QueryExplorerAPIContract-Endpoint">Endp=
oint</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"77=
6e7f24-b229-4a86-848f-17b545211cad" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d41a135d-b4c2-470a-b448-7e7c50e2fbd6">
<th data-local-id=3D"9d830f3b-7a08-4522-adf7-7da6196fdd57" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ba45e0e4c642">Field</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"7c7143ae-794f-4526-8656-3ad518cd5ffb" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"129964c6c063">Value</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bc39f740-0a91-4c70-b157-ae19bf9d63ac">
<td data-local-id=3D"e9c70326-b9d8-4592-85d7-52fa7ccb491d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d412b74021c8">Method</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7d276f94-6a44-46a0-bb76-4bacfea1ef98" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9a7745446b15"><code>POST</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"76ca6e2c-e1a7-4486-bb73-575f8aab1ae0">
<td data-local-id=3D"b4a57b11-4186-4595-934b-013c361b8107" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa41c2293f09">Path</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6990fc83-88b6-4217-b536-5b96da864454" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ff8bbc86ffb6"><code>/query</code></p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2a09b926-e796-45e3-b282-f8e09a2ef6f4">
<td data-local-id=3D"2ae68b6d-eb17-4cfd-bb5d-53aa9bbc33c9" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bbe9a91d995e">Content-Type</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"75c8acb6-17ec-4c94-b288-1a8a36172f37" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fe1e67f42f11"><code>application/json</code></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h1 local-id=3D"d13bf832c24f" id=3D"QueryExplorerAPIContract-RequestFormat"=
>Request Format</h1>
<p local-id=3D"b88c577238c6">The frontend sends queries using a <strong>Gra=
phQL-style request body</strong>.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "query": "query GetArtefacts($repo: String!, $ref: String!, $path: String=
!) { repo(name: $repo) { ref(name: $ref) { file(path: $path) { artefacts { =
symbolFqn canonicalKind } } } } }",
  "variables": {
    "repo": "repo1",
    "ref": "main",
    "path": "src/auth/service.ts"
  },
  "operationName": "GetArtefacts"
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"b8129145-5802-4905-947b-25f534881940">
